  "exec_summary": [
    "GrowthBook clicks slipped 4.3% week-over-week (3,418 vs. 3,572), but the headline number is less alarming than it looks. The homepage alone accounts for 1,770 clicks this week vs. 1,851 last week, an 81-click drop that is almost certainly branded search noise, not a meaningful organic loss. Impressions actually grew 5.5% (110,304 vs. 104,554), signaling improving crawl coverage. The AI testing guide (/blog/how-to-a-b-test-ai-a-practical-guide/) had the strongest momentum, jumping from 1 to 10 clicks, and the LaunchDarkly comparison page doubled from 4 to 8 clicks.",
    "The single most important finding this week is Amplitude's aggressive push into comparison and category pages. Four of the top five opportunities are Amplitude-owned URLs targeting high-intent queries like 'best feature flag tools for startups,' 'best mobile AB testing for developers,' and 'top AB testing platforms.' These are exactly the queries that capture buyers at the moment of evaluation, and GrowthBook has no direct content competing for them. Amplitude is effectively owning the comparison layer of the funnel for GrowthBook's core audience.",
    "No new competitor content was published this week in the feature flags or experimentation space that registered as a surge, and LaunchDarkly's core feature flags page remains the top-ranked threat at KD 38. The quiet week from competitors is a window to move on the Amplitude comparison gaps before they compound further."
  ],
